Singer Ayanda Jiya has reflected on her journey that saw her lose everything, but she maintains it wasn't for nothing. Despite this, she is adamant that she will never drop her crown because it's part of life. Taking to her Twitter account, she shared her story while encouraging her followers to "always wear their crowns". "Life Neh... We go through so much. We lose all sorts of things. Houses, cars, jobs, friends, family. I lost everything. But I refuse to believe it's for nothing. Regardless, be encouraged and keep my chin up. Queens wear crowns and I'll be damned if I were to drop mine," she captioned a picture of herself. 